Nov 18 2009 	A grand dame reawakens in splendor	The Pierre is one of New York's most iconic hotels and the Taj group have done a wonderful job in restoring the property to its former glory. I stayed for a few nights in early November and could not have been more enchanted. The location has always been beyond perfect, but the refurbishment that has been brought to both the public spaces and rooms is a great success. I very much enjoyed the classic yet contemporary feel in the rooms and was impressed with how the bathrooms had been reconfigured. The lobby atmosphere is lovely and only improved by the very charming staff that you come across throughout the hotel. A particular mention must go to the best elevator operators ever! I also shouldn't forget to say that the new restaurant Caprice and the new lobby bar appear to be quite the hot spots as both were busy well into the evening, even on nights earlier in the week when I was staying there. Overall, I hope Taj maintains the impressive efforts currently in place; if so the Pierre will be my only choice in New York.	
Nov 17 2009 	Absolutely Charming	I had a fantastic stay at The Pierre. I live in New York City and I am quite familiar with the local 5 star hotels, but my company recently put me up here during a conference that I attended so I decided to experience the city as a tourist. Check in was fast and easy (it probably helped that my company was footing the bill) and I was escorted to my room by a young lady who was charming and a great ambassador to the hotel. I have to say that I was impressed that the hotel still maintains its 'old-world' charm by employing elevator operators (who couldn't be more friendly) and by having maintained most of the architectural details during its recent renovation (I really enjoyed that they still have a functional mail chute, expansive marble lobby, and crown moldings throughout the building). The room was elegant and modern at the same time with beautiful furniture of a quality that I am not used to seeing in hotel rooms. The bathroom was fabulous with seperate tub and fully enclosed rain shower that I never wanted to step out of. The bed was perhaps one of my favorite aspects of the stay. I slept better there than in my own apartment. I didn't try room service but I ate in the lobby lounge, which has a small menu in addition to a surprisingly reasonably priced cocktail menu. Try the Gin Gin. It has fresh cucumbers and it is amazing. I've already been back to the lounge with friends and this drink is a real hit all around. I really must highly recommend this hotel. While I was inside, I felt like I was transported to a different time where 5 star hospitality was more than just flat screen televisions, pretentious attitudes and high prices.	
