Apr 19 2005	Magnificent Hotel	A fabulous hotel. We would absolutely stay here again. The hotel is all about service and elegance and succeeds at both. The staff is professional and attentive. A great place to stay.	
Mar 23 2005	Don't believe many of these negative reviews	It all has to do with expectations. If you're a self-important jerk who thinks the world revolves around you and if you demand nothing less than perfection from the staff of every hotel you visit, then the Pierre isn't for you. And neither are most fine hotels. But the Pierre works quite nicely for me.My wife, kids (ages 7,4, and 2) and I stay at the Pierre a few times a year and absolutely love it. We love the staff who seem to take a genuine interest in us and our children. Remarkably, the staff has changed very little over the years and we know many of them by now. The rooms are very nice and large by New York standards with lovely marble bathrooms and nice amenities. The hotel has an &quot;old New York&quot; feel and is quite grand (especially at Christmas), but I wouldn't describe it as dated or tired at all.The location is great. We love to stroll through the upper east side and shop. The kids love the fact that the park is right across the street and we usually stop by the Central Park Zoo, which is minutes away from the hotel. For families, the hotel has a great package that gives you two adjoining rooms, breakfast, milk&amp;cookies for the kids, treat bags/games for the kids, candy box from Dylan's, all for about $700/night.I've stayed in other grand NYC hotels (Carlyle, St. Regis, Plaza, Waldorf) and liked them all, but the Pierre is my personal favorite	
Feb 27 2005	Like Your Favorite Old Cashmere Sweater	Like your most comfortable old cashmere sweater, the Pierre wears like it fit from the first day you tried it on. Quiet, comfortable, and yes, old-fashioned, everything is done to make you feel like the most important guest of the moment. For the standard corporate rack rate, we got a huge room with sitting area, a large double-sink bathroom and the most comfortable bed we've ever slept in. The Cafe Pierre with it's faux-rococo ante-room provides a calm, unrushed oasis of murmuring service with steaming hot tea or icy cold martini's in an adult manner and atmosphere where you can actually hear yourselves think and just barely hear the rustle of your neighbor's mink. Ladies, get a pedicure from Ines in the Salon Dominique, and Gentlemen, if you want the shave of a lifetime, ask for Robertina. The main thing is, take your time to enjoy the hotel, and you will definitely want to return.	
