Jan 23 2005	Old style Fifth Avenue hotel	Stayed at the Pierre for 3 nights. Wonderful old style boutique hotel on Fifth Avenue opposite Central Park - fantastic location. Room was spacious and comfortable with traditional decor. If you want a modern hotel - this one is not for you! My wife loved the Bulgari bathroom products. Slight hiccup one day when the room lock malfunctioned and the lower door panel had to be removed so we could clamber out! Staff were extremely apologetic, however, and gave us 50% off that night's tariff. If you want to experience traditional style Fifth Avenue we would definitely reccomend this hotel.	
Jan 19 2005	Pleasantly surprised	Stayed here for 2 nights this past weekend, and was pleasantly surprised. (I must said that after reading most of the negative reviews I was not expecting much) The staff was professional and anxious to help, up to Four Seasons standards. The room was large enough to make the king size bed look small (unlike my experiences at the Waldorf or Marriot Westside), except the TV was tiny, I don't think it was even a 19 inch. Everything seemed clean and new, and the bed was the most comfortable I've slept in. My only complaint is that it was very noisy, throughout the night I can hear machinery sounds( the elevator?), I'm a heavy sleeper and it sure bothered me, I can't imagine what it would be like to a light sleeper. Overall I would recommend this hotel, especially the location can't be beat if your plans include shopping in the fancy stores.	
Nov 14 2004	Adequate but not stellar!	My husband and I stayed at The Pierre for a week in September. The location, of course, is great. But I found the hotel a but &quot;stuffy&quot; and pretentious. I don't care for elevator operators (after all, if I can't push my own floor button, I should stay home!!). The room (jr suite) was very nice and spacious, but it was pricey. I would not stay there again. I would rather try a different hotel, or go back to my favorite--The Michaelangelo over on 51st and 7th Avenue.	
Sep 5 2004 	There Are Many Betters Hotels for The Money	I love the location of this hotel. However, that's about it. I went for a quick overnight business trip, and wound up in a room not much bigger than a walk in closet. Although it was clean, and it was apparent that the hotel had tried to make it confom to Four Seasons standards, it is not even remotely close to say, the Four Seasons Chicago, or the Four Seasons Toronto, or other Four Seasons Hotels. Based upon my experience, this is, at best, a 3 star hotel. Frankly, given its wonderful location, they just need to gut the whole place and bring it into the 21st century with decent sized rooms and elevators that don't creak.	
